In [94]:
# To impute missing values for all numerical variables using the mean
df.fillna(df.select_dtypes(include=['number']).mean(), inplace=True)

# For categorical columns, fill with mode
for column in df.select_dtypes(include=['object', 'category']).columns:
    df[column].fillna(df[column].mode()[0], inplace=True)

# Calculate the value counts and their  percentage of genders
outcome_counts = df['Gender'].value_counts()
outcome_percentage = outcome_counts / outcome_counts.sum() * 100

# Create the bar chart
ax = outcome_counts.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(8, 6))

# Set title and labels
plt.title('Bar Chart for Outcome Column with Percentages')
plt.xlabel('Gender')
plt.ylabel('Count')

# Add percentages on top of bars
for i, count in enumerate(outcome_counts):
    ax.text(i, count + 5, f'{outcome_percentage[i]:.2f}%', ha='center', fontsize=12)

# Show the plot
plt.show()

# Calculate the percentage distribution of Spending Score by Gender
gender_spending_pct = df.groupby('Gender')['Spending_Score'].value_counts(normalize=True).unstack() * 100

# Plot the boxplot
plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
sns.boxplot(x='Gender', y='Spending_Score', data=df, palette='pastel')

# Adding percentages as annotations
for i, gender in enumerate(gender_spending_pct.index):
    for j, score in enumerate(gender_spending_pct.columns):
        # Adjust the position of the annotations as needed
        plt.text(i, j, f"{gender_spending_pct.loc[gender, score]:.1f}%", 
                 horizontalalignment='center', verticalalignment='center', fontsize=12)

# Customizing the plot
plt.title('Purchase Amount by Gender (with Percentages)')
plt.xlabel('Gender')
plt.ylabel('Spending Score')
plt.show()

df['spending_numeric'] = pd.to_numeric(df['spending_numeric'], errors='coerce')

# Group by 'Gender' and sum the 'spending_numeric' values
gender_spend = df.groupby('Gender')['spending_numeric'].sum()

# Calculate the total spend
total_spend = gender_spend.sum()

# Calculate the percentage spend for each gender
gender_percentage = (gender_spend / total_spend) * 100

# Show the result
print(gender_percentage)
